{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["Lightly grease a pie dish (22 cm) and set aside.","Place icing sugar into mixing bowl and sift <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>.","Add plain flour, salt and butter and blend <strong> <nobr>10 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr><\/strong>. Mixture should resemble breadcrumbs.","Knead <nobr>30 sec\/<\/nobr>, adding egg yolks 1 at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid.","Transfer dough onto ThermoMat or floured surface and work into a tight ball. Wrap in plastic wrap then place into the refrigerator for minimum 15 minutes or until chilled.","Once chilled, transfer pastry onto ThermoMat or floured work surface then roll out pastry to line your pie dish. Transfer pastry to prepared pie dish and remove any excess pastry hanging over the edges. Ensure there are no tears or holes in the pastry. Place into refrigerator to rest for 30 minutes.","Preheat oven to 180°C. Line chilled pastry base with baking paper then fill with pie weights or beans. Blind bake for 15 minutes (180°C) on the bottom shelf of the oven until slightly golden. Remove baking paper and pie weights or beans and bake for a further 10 minutes (180°C), until golden brown and cooked through. Set pastry aside and allow to cool."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Place lemon zest and caster sugar into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add lemon juice and butter and heat <nobr>3 min\/60°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Mix <nobr>45-50 sec\/speed 2<\/nobr>, adding eggs 1 at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid. Once eggs are incorporated, cook <nobr>7 min\/80°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Filling will thicken as it cooks. Set cooked filling aside. Thoroughly clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Meringue","content":["Increase oven temperature to 200°C."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk. <\/strong>Place egg whites and cream of tartar into mixing bowl and whip <nobr>3-4 min\/50°C\/speed 3.5<\/nobr> until stiff peaks form.","Mix <nobr>4 min\/50°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>, adding icing sugar 1 tbsp at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid <strong>.<\/strong> ","Transfer lemon filling into cooked pastry case and gently smooth over the top.  Spread meringue on top of lemon filling and use a spoon to make soft peaks.  Bake for 5 minutes (200°C) until meringue is lightly browned. Remove from oven and allow to cool (approx. 30 minutes) then transfer in to the refrigerator to chill for minimum 1 hour. Slice and serve chilled."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["100 g unsalted butter, chilled, cut into pieces, plus extra for greasing","50 g icing sugar","230 g plain flour","1 pinch salt, to taste","3 egg yolks"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["1 lemon, zest only, no white pith","100 g caster sugar","220 g lemon juice (approx. 6 - 7 lemons)","65 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces","6 eggs"]},{"title":"Meringue","content":["4 egg whites, room temperature","¼ tsp cream of tartar","150 g icing sugar"]}],"id":"r68948","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-klPLHHW08eo\/XZanZfGbUdI\/AAAAAAAAg-c\/Bz87BA1-8HML-7dWH0TskQ6J1Cyn9HpVQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Euje2pN9tTDZEGbL.png","title":"Lemon meringue pie","publishedAt":"2014-09-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"8 g","fat":"15 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"40 g","calories":"1371 kJ \/ 326 kcal"},"usefulItems":"pie dish (22 cm), ThermoMat, plastic wrap, rolling pin, baking paper, pie weights, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Lemon meringue pie is a great dessert or special treat at afternoon tea.","You can also use a kitchen blow torch to caramelise your meringue, if you have one.","Mill icing sugar in your Thermomix to use in this recipe.","Retain the leftover egg yolk from this recipe to use in custard or mayonnaise."],"basicInfo":["advanced","35m","3h","12 portions"]}